    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required credibility level. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 1 vs. required 2) reflects a constraint of the ASTM F1717 standardized test method and is consistent with FDA-accepted practice for Class II spinal implants. All three pre-specified QoI acceptance criteria were met (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for the COU.",
